/td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Looking for a PC and some personal opinions on this spell. On Luclin its going for 1-2k. <br>
<br>
I'm told this is an excellent animation to have but I'm having a hard time justifying spending that kind of plat when the lvl 62 animation is only going for 50-100pp. I just don't know if its worth it. <br>
<br>
Thanks! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/Hydrus/hydrus_signiture.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=731114">My Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub3.ezboard.com/bpossums">Possums</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emmietheenchantress>Emmie The Enchantress</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(8/2/03 3:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w1.404.telia.com/~u40405647/inu-yasha/faces.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Zumaik's Animation does have a noticable improvement over the animation that comes before it; however, you can still use your lower-level summoned pet still to do your bidding just fine.  There is no need to spend 1k-2k on a spell such as your summoned pet spell (in my opinion), anyway.<br>
<br>
If you really like to solo using your summoned pets and it's important to you, however, then Zumaik's Animation is something you might want to look into getting (and hopefully for a better price, of course!).  Otherwise, I would just wait until you can use your level 62 pet, which is inexpensive, a huge improvement, and a pet that you can use for more than knocking down green mobs.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=optimisticfool>Optimistic Fool</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(8/4/03 1:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Why don't you use your research skill to combine the spell yourself? You need keris page 7, left and right. The pages usually sell much cheaper then the scroll. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barahil>barahil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(8/4/03 7:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Zumaik's Animation</span><hr size=1> Actually, Keri page 7 left and right is Illusion Vah Shir.  I made a number of those spells using that recipie.  I can't say what the animation components are though right now.  I used a list on eq.castersrealm.com but that's still down I think. <p>Barahil Bedazzler<br>
